documentation.text:
@notice Buy a Nft.
 @dev Buy NFT function. Transfer the NFT to the msg.sender.
 Requirements:
 - The Nft is listed to sale,
 - Cannot buy your own NFT.
 - Send the good amount.
 Emits a {Buyed} event.

devdoc.author: JWMatheo - member of NFTSet Team
devdoc.details: NFT marketplace contract. You need to deploy FactoryV3.sol first and implement the Factory address.

DeployMyNFTCollection(string,string,stri.details: Deploy a NFT collection . Can be impove by letting user set his own _salt. Emits a {Showed} event.

addItemToCollection(address).details: Triggers 'mint' function in the collection address '_thisCollection'.

params._thisCollection: The collection address in wich the nft is added.

buyToken(uint256).details: Buy NFT function. Transfer the NFT to the msg.sender. Requirements: - The Nft is listed to sale, - Cannot buy your own NFT. - Send the good amount. Emits a {Buyed} event.

cancel(uint256).details: Cancel a listed to sale NFT. Transfer back the NFT from Marketplace to the msg.sender. Requirements: - Only seller can cancel listing, - The NFT is listed to sale. Emits a {Cancelled} event.

getListOfNFTfromUser(address).details: Get an array wich contains a structure for each NFT purchased && currently owned.

returns._0: MyBuyedNFT[] The array wich contains a structure for each NFT purchased && currently owned.

getListing(uint256).details: Get the structure from mapping a listed NFT Id.

params.listingId: The listed NFT Id to check.

returns._0: Listing structure of the entered listed NFT Id.

getSellActivity(uint256).details: Get an array wich contains all addresses having been in possession of the listed nft.

params.listingId: The listed NFT Id to check.

returns._0: address[] The array which contains all addresses having been in possession of the listed nft.

getUserCollections(address).details: Get an array wich contains all collection address created for a given address.

returns._0: address[] The array which contains all colection address.

listToken(uint256,uint256).details: Set a price and status to make the NFT buyable then transfer the NFT to the marketplace. Requirements: - 'msg.sender' is the owner of the tokenId 'listing.tokenId' at address 'listing.tokenContract' - The Nft is not already listed to sale Emits a {Listed} event.

showToken(address,uint256).details: Create a 'Listing' structure to make your NFT appear in the marketplace. '_defaultPrice' in 'Listing' is set to prevent a potentially vulnerability attack. Requirements: - 'msg.sender' is the owner of the tokenId '_tokenId' at address '_tokenContract' Emits a {Showed} event.
